<br>
They've diminished our contribution and &quot;fun factor&quot; as a class by:<br>
<br>
1) Going to huge negative resist modifiers throughout PoP and beyond, making the contribution of AE resist songs less important (remember how important we were in NToV?)<br>
<br>
2) Giving speed-cap level mounts to knights <br>
<br>
3) Giving group atk buffs to shadowknights that exceeds the contribution of a bard in DPS groups<br>
<br>
4) Reducing the duration and resist modifier of our mezzes<br>
<br>
5) Capping the target level of our charm song below that of the mobs we kill to xp<br>
<br>
Fadind memories gave us a new role in PoP.  I can understand monks concern, but they've since improved monk abilities so they are every bit as viable a puller as a bard in most situations and better pullers in many.  Nerfing fading memories will nearly cripple bards as a pulling class.<br>
<br>
Nerfing fading memories will reduce bard utility and the overall &quot;fun&quot; factor of the class by a huge degree.  There comes a point where designers change a class so much by a single nerf that members of that class will just be bitter as can be going forward.  I won't play my bard at that point, and a serious FM nerf is that point for Harmonae.<br>
<br>
I seriously hope the design team reconsiders this.  Other threads have discussed the attrition rate for bards since GoD came out - many guilds are having trouble maintaining a viable bard &quot;core&quot;.  Pretty sure this change will firmly put bards in the &quot;endangered species&quot; category. <p><p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=365770> <center><img src="http://www.geocities.com/latuttle/harmsig2.jpg"></center> </img> </a></p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=harmonae>Harmonae</A> at: 6/7/04 9:18 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#330000>- </font><a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall>The Concert Hall - Message Boards</a><font color=#330000> - </font><a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage>Backstage</a><font color=#330000> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.31q<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  